WEBVTT

00:00:01.856 --> 00:00:03.733
Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.

00:00:05.110 --> 00:00:07.237
People who have used these drugs

00:00:07.320 --> 00:00:10.824
are now estimated
to total two million in Japan.

00:00:11.366 --> 00:00:14.452
The number of people arrested
for drug-related offenses

00:00:15.036 --> 00:00:17.038
is as many as 14,000 yearly.

00:00:18.289 --> 00:00:20.458
This is what you'll suggest to Kurosaki.

00:00:20.542 --> 00:00:21.918
"Let's get not just Nagata,

00:00:22.001 --> 00:00:25.296
but also the organization
that was selling drugs to him.

00:00:25.380 --> 00:00:27.924
I'll go and investigate
their smuggling routes."

00:00:28.007 --> 00:00:30.176
You think Kurosaki would fall for that?

00:00:30.260 --> 00:00:31.970
You little shit.

00:00:32.637 --> 00:00:35.014
How about we go for an eyeball?

00:00:35.098 --> 00:00:35.932
Don't!

00:00:36.015 --> 00:00:40.145
The Saeki Family that's been looking
after us needs some more manpower.

00:00:41.855 --> 00:00:42.814
You.

00:00:43.439 --> 00:00:45.358
Go help them for a few days.

00:00:45.441 --> 00:00:46.401
Listen up.

00:00:46.484 --> 00:00:49.904
One look at how they clean
and I can tell if they're useful.

00:00:49.988 --> 00:00:52.574
If they seem trustworthy,
they'll get the goods.

00:00:52.657 --> 00:00:54.325
Shouldn't be a bad deal.

00:00:54.868 --> 00:00:55.743
Yes, sir.

00:00:55.827 --> 00:00:57.829
-Right, Shinichi?
-I'm Shinji, sir.

00:00:57.912 --> 00:00:59.914
Does it fucking matter?

00:01:00.665 --> 00:01:03.042
-I'm Shinichi--
-You too!

00:01:03.543 --> 00:01:07.297
If I infiltrate it, we can grasp
the entire flow of the cocaine.

00:01:07.380 --> 00:01:08.423
With this plan,

00:01:08.506 --> 00:01:12.427
we can get more than just the people
who directly sold the cocaine to Nagata.

00:01:12.510 --> 00:01:13.887
The client list.

00:01:13.970 --> 00:01:16.848
Search for it. Find it. Bring it.
That's my condition.

00:01:19.350 --> 00:01:20.560
Hello, sir!

00:01:24.522 --> 00:01:26.024
Did you wipe all of this?

00:01:26.107 --> 00:01:27.817
Sorry, it was me.

00:01:30.612 --> 00:01:31.988
You pass.

00:01:32.071 --> 00:01:32.906
What?

00:01:32.989 --> 00:01:35.950
Go to the dock right now
and collect our monthly shipment.

00:01:36.034 --> 00:01:37.160
What kind of shipment?

00:01:37.952 --> 00:01:39.203
Cocaine.

00:01:39.954 --> 00:01:42.040
Someone else will handle the payment.

00:01:42.123 --> 00:01:45.126
You just get the shipment
and contact me immediately.

00:01:45.209 --> 00:01:47.712
-Ask Shinichi the details.
-Yes, sir.

00:01:52.091 --> 00:01:53.676
I just received the goods.

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:55.678
Take them to the address I'm sending you.

00:01:55.762 --> 00:01:56.763
Yes, sir.

00:01:56.846 --> 00:01:58.723
SAEKI SEAFOOD COMPANY

00:01:58.806 --> 00:01:59.849
You still a newbie?

00:01:59.933 --> 00:02:00.892
Just be quick.

00:02:00.975 --> 00:02:03.686
I always get it done on time.

00:02:09.692 --> 00:02:11.236
Hey, you're in the way. Move.

00:02:11.319 --> 00:02:12.320
Sorry.

00:02:46.229 --> 00:02:49.190
Come to Parking Lot #5
in the Bay Area right now.

00:02:49.273 --> 00:02:51.401
I found the Saeki Family's cocaine route.

00:02:53.111 --> 00:02:54.904
Did the NCD find it that quick?

00:02:55.488 --> 00:02:57.782
No, I found it on my own.

00:02:59.158 --> 00:03:01.119
They already trust you that much?

00:03:01.202 --> 00:03:02.829
They smuggle it from overseas,

00:03:02.912 --> 00:03:05.748
collect it on fishing boats,
and hide it in the fish.

00:03:06.249 --> 00:03:08.084
They deliver those to fishmongers,

00:03:08.167 --> 00:03:10.712
and take the cocaine
to apartments they've rented.

00:03:10.795 --> 00:03:11.963
Got it.

00:03:12.630 --> 00:03:13.673
Where are the goods?

00:03:13.756 --> 00:03:14.882
I have them.

00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:18.136
Even if we don't leak
more info to the NCD,

00:03:18.219 --> 00:03:20.096
this should be enough as evidence.

00:03:20.972 --> 00:03:22.140
That's true.

00:03:22.223 --> 00:03:24.934
Come before the Saeki guys get suspicious.

00:03:25.018 --> 00:03:26.686
I'll hide nearby with the coke.

00:03:26.769 --> 00:03:29.063
All right. I'll arrange it immediately.

00:03:29.147 --> 00:03:31.482
That's mission accomplished, right?

00:03:35.486 --> 00:03:37.113
Great job.

00:03:54.505 --> 00:03:55.965
What are you up to?

00:04:54.565 --> 00:04:57.568
SAEKI SEAFOOD COMPANY

00:05:02.740 --> 00:05:05.910
Did ya really think
cleaning would earn you trust?

00:05:05.993 --> 00:05:09.580
I thought you were suspicious
as hell right from the start.

00:05:15.169 --> 00:05:17.296
Who ordered you to steal our goods?

00:05:18.756 --> 00:05:19.799
I told you.

00:05:20.842 --> 00:05:21.759
That's not it.

00:05:21.843 --> 00:05:23.845
What else would it be?!

00:05:23.928 --> 00:05:25.930
What are you and Matsubara scheming?

00:05:26.514 --> 00:05:27.432
Matsubara?

00:05:28.015 --> 00:05:29.267
Hey, bring him in.

00:05:29.350 --> 00:05:30.476
Sir.

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.603
Aren't you a dealer for Matsubara?

00:05:33.354 --> 00:05:34.772
-Yes.
-Come here, you.

00:05:34.856 --> 00:05:35.940
Get in there.

00:05:37.108 --> 00:05:38.609
Get a move on!

00:05:38.693 --> 00:05:39.861
Mr. Matsubara!

00:05:43.906 --> 00:05:45.575
Umezawa.

00:05:46.367 --> 00:05:49.245
What the hell did you do?

00:05:49.745 --> 00:05:50.997
No, I didn't--

00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:53.583
Hey! Drop the cheap act!

00:05:53.666 --> 00:05:57.128
You two tried to steal
our goods, didn't you?

00:05:58.421 --> 00:05:59.297
No.

00:06:00.006 --> 00:06:01.883
It wasn't me.

00:06:01.966 --> 00:06:04.218
He did it all on his own.

00:06:07.722 --> 00:06:12.602
You think a punk like this has the balls
to steal from the yakuza on his own?

00:06:13.227 --> 00:06:15.646
And you're not much
better than him yourself.

00:06:19.150 --> 00:06:21.194
Whose orders are you two following?

00:06:21.277 --> 00:06:22.612
Spit it out already.

00:06:27.575 --> 00:06:28.951
I swear…

00:06:32.079 --> 00:06:33.414
I didn't know about this.

00:06:45.092 --> 00:06:47.553
Umezawa!

00:06:48.304 --> 00:06:50.431
Say something, you fucker!

00:06:51.474 --> 00:06:53.517
Umezawa!

00:06:53.601 --> 00:06:55.436
I have nothing to do with this!

00:06:55.519 --> 00:06:57.939
-You bastard. Why?
-Hey.

00:06:58.022 --> 00:07:01.150
-Why are you making me go through…
-Hey!

00:07:04.028 --> 00:07:05.905
Why are you pissing in my office?

00:07:05.988 --> 00:07:08.115
You're getting the floor all filthy!

00:07:12.995 --> 00:07:15.540
I'm telling you
not to stain the damn floor!

00:07:24.465 --> 00:07:25.466
Hey, Shinji.

00:07:25.550 --> 00:07:26.467
I'm Shinichi.

00:07:26.551 --> 00:07:28.094
Who the fuck cares!

00:07:28.177 --> 00:07:30.096
Wipe the floor thoroughly later.

00:07:30.179 --> 00:07:33.140
It gets tough to clean
when the blood starts to harden.

00:07:33.224 --> 00:07:34.183
Yes, sir.

00:07:37.937 --> 00:07:40.022
Let's move on, then.

00:07:41.399 --> 00:07:43.734
Your turn next.

00:07:47.196 --> 00:07:48.781
Please forgive me!

00:07:49.615 --> 00:07:50.866
For what?

00:07:50.950 --> 00:07:53.035
What would I forgive you for?

00:07:53.119 --> 00:07:55.746
You must feel guilty
if you're asking for forgiveness.

00:07:55.830 --> 00:07:58.583
What do you want forgiveness for?

00:07:59.333 --> 00:08:01.794
I mean, this is a misunderstanding.

00:08:03.087 --> 00:08:04.547
What misunderstanding?

00:08:04.630 --> 00:08:06.924
I'm asking you why you stopped the car

00:08:07.008 --> 00:08:09.927
and checked the cargo
while transporting the goods.

00:08:10.678 --> 00:08:11.804
Because…

00:08:13.889 --> 00:08:17.435
I got worried whether the goods
were still there or got stolen.

00:08:17.518 --> 00:08:18.477
The heck?

00:08:18.561 --> 00:08:21.480
How would anyone steal them
from a moving vehicle?

00:08:21.564 --> 00:08:23.566
Why would you suddenly worry about that?

00:08:23.649 --> 00:08:27.528
And what did you do after stopping
the car and taking out the fish, huh?

00:08:27.612 --> 00:08:28.988
Answer, damn it!

00:08:31.365 --> 00:08:34.994
I'm the type to get worried
if I don't double-check things!

00:08:36.120 --> 00:08:39.999
Like whether I turned the lights off
or locked my door when I go out.

00:08:40.082 --> 00:08:42.627
I would even go back home
to check sometimes.

00:08:43.461 --> 00:08:44.920
Don't you ever do that?

00:08:47.923 --> 00:08:49.216
All the time.

00:08:50.051 --> 00:08:52.637
Did you think that dumb excuse would work?

00:08:54.847 --> 00:08:57.600
Only two more centimeters to your heart.

00:08:57.683 --> 00:08:58.809
Strange, isn't it?

00:08:58.893 --> 00:09:03.731
You're talking just fine right now,
but if I come any closer, you're dead.

00:09:04.607 --> 00:09:07.485
How about it? Want to try dying once?

00:09:12.198 --> 00:09:13.491
Is this the place?

00:09:13.574 --> 00:09:15.284
Who the hell are you?

00:09:18.287 --> 00:09:19.205
Freeze!

00:09:20.873 --> 00:09:21.957
Freeze!

00:09:22.833 --> 00:09:24.001
Who are you?

00:09:25.086 --> 00:09:27.588
I'm with the NCD.
I'll shoot if you resist.

00:09:32.843 --> 00:09:33.886
You're bluffing.

00:09:33.969 --> 00:09:36.597
I'm not. I repeat.
I'll shoot if you resist.

00:09:36.681 --> 00:09:37.807
Get on the ground.

00:09:37.890 --> 00:09:39.600
Man up, Shinichi. Go.

00:09:39.684 --> 00:09:40.643
Yes, sir.

00:09:48.734 --> 00:09:50.403
I'm dead serious.

00:09:52.863 --> 00:09:53.989
Shit.

00:09:57.159 --> 00:09:58.202
How did you find me?

00:09:58.285 --> 00:09:59.620
GPS tracker.

00:10:03.708 --> 00:10:04.667
Take this.

00:10:06.001 --> 00:10:07.461
What's this, all of a sudden?

00:10:07.545 --> 00:10:08.796
A good luck charm.

00:10:09.422 --> 00:10:11.716
What gives? You're creeping me out.

00:10:12.591 --> 00:10:14.927
You'll have to protect yourself.

00:10:15.010 --> 00:10:16.637
You weren't trying to be nice?

00:10:17.763 --> 00:10:19.098
The charm?

00:10:19.181 --> 00:10:22.059
Yeah, it's not like
I trusted you completely.

00:10:24.687 --> 00:10:25.646
The whole time?

00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:27.481
Yeah.

00:10:28.315 --> 00:10:30.401
NAKANO EAST AVENUE

00:10:33.404 --> 00:10:35.156
SAEKI SEAFOOD COMPANY

00:10:35.239 --> 00:10:36.073
Wait a second.

00:10:36.657 --> 00:10:38.075
There were guards outside.

00:10:38.743 --> 00:10:40.494
They won't be moving for a while.

00:10:47.042 --> 00:10:49.170
-What do you want?
-Stop right there.

00:10:49.253 --> 00:10:50.171
-Move.
-Fuck you!

00:11:27.082 --> 00:11:28.125
Damn it.

00:11:29.585 --> 00:11:32.213
Couldn't you have saved me sooner?

00:11:32.296 --> 00:11:33.964
I thought I was going to die!

00:11:34.048 --> 00:11:36.884
I told you,
you would have to protect yourself.

00:11:37.843 --> 00:11:38.928
Come on…

00:11:39.762 --> 00:11:41.388
I'll say it again.

00:11:42.473 --> 00:11:43.724
Get on the ground.

00:11:45.184 --> 00:11:46.060
Watch out!

00:11:53.901 --> 00:11:56.487
Don't let your guard down
in a yakuza office.

00:12:10.334 --> 00:12:11.502
How can you still move?

00:12:12.127 --> 00:12:14.338
This isn't enough to put me down!

00:12:14.421 --> 00:12:15.422
I knew it.

00:12:16.006 --> 00:12:18.259
You were doing speed, weren't you?

00:12:18.342 --> 00:12:20.135
Taking from the goods?

00:12:20.219 --> 00:12:21.720
Damn junkie zombie.

00:12:21.804 --> 00:12:22.888
Get him!

00:12:31.939 --> 00:12:33.023
Don't move!

00:12:33.774 --> 00:12:34.817
Or he dies.

00:12:48.789 --> 00:12:50.708
Fucking bastard.

00:12:58.632 --> 00:12:59.800
Kurosaki.

00:13:07.474 --> 00:13:09.727
What do we do with him?

00:13:10.644 --> 00:13:12.313
Good question.

00:13:13.355 --> 00:13:15.899
We can't just let him go like this.

00:13:16.942 --> 00:13:18.569
Guess we have to kill him.

00:13:19.278 --> 00:13:21.447
But killing a narcotics agent…

00:13:21.530 --> 00:13:23.407
What other choice is there?

00:13:23.490 --> 00:13:24.450
Okay, sir.

00:13:24.533 --> 00:13:26.160
Is the other guy taken care of?

00:13:26.243 --> 00:13:27.202
Yes.

00:13:27.286 --> 00:13:28.579
Shinji went to do it.

00:13:39.632 --> 00:13:40.841
We're back.

00:13:41.467 --> 00:13:46.096
We checked with the police,
and the body is confirmed to be Nagata's.

00:13:46.180 --> 00:13:50.434
I won't tell a soul
that I bought from the Saeki Family!

00:13:50.517 --> 00:13:53.145
Please, have mercy on me!

00:13:55.314 --> 00:13:57.149
Any word from Kurosaki?

00:13:57.232 --> 00:13:58.817
Nothing yet.

00:14:00.694 --> 00:14:04.239
What is he doing, all while
ignoring calls from his superior?

00:14:05.491 --> 00:14:07.409
He hasn't read our messages either.

00:14:07.493 --> 00:14:08.577
What should we do?

00:14:08.661 --> 00:14:11.455
If an agent stops making
their scheduled check-ins,

00:14:11.538 --> 00:14:13.707
we're supposed to report it
to our higher-ups,

00:14:13.791 --> 00:14:16.377
considering the chance
they might have been attacked.

00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:18.962
We would do so for anyone other than him,

00:14:19.046 --> 00:14:22.341
but in his case,
he's probably just ignoring the rules.

00:14:22.424 --> 00:14:24.468
No doubt about it.

00:14:25.177 --> 00:14:28.764
Damn it, will he ever stop
acting like a loose cannon?

00:14:31.016 --> 00:14:32.142
Could it be

00:14:32.226 --> 00:14:35.646
that he went back to the hospital
to continue questioning Kaga?

00:14:36.146 --> 00:14:37.940
He does tend to be stubborn.

00:14:45.072 --> 00:14:45.948
Let's move.

00:14:59.837 --> 00:15:01.005
Oh, sorry.

00:15:14.768 --> 00:15:16.103
Oh, sorry.

00:15:17.229 --> 00:15:19.982
-The doctor just now. Inaba, find him.
-Yes, sir.

00:15:20.065 --> 00:15:21.275
Aoshima, call a nurse.

00:15:21.358 --> 00:15:22.317
-Okay!
-The nurse call?

00:15:22.985 --> 00:15:24.945
-It's right there.
-Okay.

00:15:25.029 --> 00:15:26.655
How many will die?

00:15:27.322 --> 00:15:29.116
What the heck is he up to?

00:15:41.754 --> 00:15:42.838
Help me with this.

00:15:43.505 --> 00:15:44.715
I'm coming.

00:15:45.591 --> 00:15:46.675
Shinji.

00:15:47.634 --> 00:15:49.386
You got Kaga, right?

00:15:50.012 --> 00:15:51.013
Yeah.

00:15:51.847 --> 00:15:53.432
We can't turn back anymore.

00:15:53.515 --> 00:15:55.184
What's going to happen to us?

00:15:55.267 --> 00:15:57.269
Calm down, would you?

00:15:58.187 --> 00:16:01.148
The boss made the call,
so we've got no choice.

00:16:01.231 --> 00:16:05.903
But I can't… murder someone.

00:16:05.986 --> 00:16:08.405
You just came back from killing one!

00:16:08.489 --> 00:16:11.492
But all I did was put drugs in his IV bag!

00:16:11.575 --> 00:16:14.078
-That's no different!
-It is.

00:16:14.161 --> 00:16:17.956
Killing someone directly is way worse
than killing them with drugs!

00:16:19.833 --> 00:16:21.710
It's still murder in the end.

00:16:23.921 --> 00:16:25.172
Seriously?

00:16:26.590 --> 00:16:27.674
Now, come on.

00:16:28.675 --> 00:16:30.094
Do as the boss said.

00:16:31.303 --> 00:16:33.305
Beat him to death with these bats.

00:16:33.388 --> 00:16:34.223
No!

00:16:34.306 --> 00:16:35.224
I don't want to!

00:16:35.891 --> 00:16:38.018
Drug them, club them,
what's the difference?

00:16:38.727 --> 00:16:41.355
Well, you would rather kill
a cockroach with insect spray

00:16:41.438 --> 00:16:43.107
than squash one, right?

00:16:43.190 --> 00:16:45.234
At least we can't see his face!

00:16:45.317 --> 00:16:46.151
Now, do it!

00:16:47.152 --> 00:16:49.446
You do it first.

00:16:50.072 --> 00:16:51.240
You're the elder brother.

00:16:51.323 --> 00:16:52.908
Then you have to do what I say.

00:16:52.991 --> 00:16:54.326
Now, do it.

00:16:54.409 --> 00:16:55.536
I don't want to!

00:16:55.619 --> 00:16:57.329
You do it first, please.

00:16:59.748 --> 00:17:00.958
All right.

00:17:02.084 --> 00:17:03.752
Watch me do it.

00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:10.801
Take this!

00:17:13.804 --> 00:17:15.139
You do it too.

00:17:21.895 --> 00:17:22.771
Fuck!

00:17:23.605 --> 00:17:26.108
Hey, go for the head. Hit the damn head.

00:17:26.191 --> 00:17:28.652
You went for the stomach too!

00:17:30.696 --> 00:17:34.575
If we don't do it,
the boss will do it to us.

00:17:52.885 --> 00:17:54.219
Really now?

00:17:54.720 --> 00:17:58.098
What's a section chief
doing out in the field?

00:17:58.932 --> 00:18:00.893
I came to collect Kaga's corpse.

00:18:00.976 --> 00:18:02.728
We're not done with it yet.

00:18:02.811 --> 00:18:04.980
As I'm sure you're well aware,

00:18:05.814 --> 00:18:08.358
we get jurisdiction once a suspect dies.

00:18:11.820 --> 00:18:14.239
One of ours was aiming for Kaga.

00:18:15.115 --> 00:18:17.367
Quite the competent officer, at that.

00:18:18.994 --> 00:18:20.621
Stay out of our way, will you?

00:18:20.704 --> 00:18:22.873
You're the one getting in our way!

00:18:24.917 --> 00:18:27.753
I hear Kurosaki
jumped off the roof with Kaga.

00:18:30.964 --> 00:18:32.382
If you come any closer,

00:18:33.050 --> 00:18:34.635
I'll jump off!

00:18:35.219 --> 00:18:38.096
-He's so high he might actually do it.
-Do it.

00:18:38.180 --> 00:18:39.932
I'm not bluffing!

00:18:51.068 --> 00:18:53.320
We could arrest Kurosaki
for attempted murder.

00:18:53.403 --> 00:18:54.863
Don't be ridiculous!

00:18:54.947 --> 00:18:56.907
He risked his life to bring Kaga in!

00:18:56.990 --> 00:18:59.076
You don't get to make that call.

00:18:59.785 --> 00:19:01.453
The police do.

00:19:19.846 --> 00:19:21.682
Quite the surprise, honestly.

00:19:22.182 --> 00:19:26.353
I was almost certain you were just
planning to leech off of our business.

00:19:26.853 --> 00:19:29.147
But then a narcotics agent shows up.

00:19:30.190 --> 00:19:31.817
So who exactly are you?

00:19:32.401 --> 00:19:33.819
Another NCD agent?

00:19:33.902 --> 00:19:37.364
Or just a dog supplying info to that man?

00:19:37.447 --> 00:19:38.532
Which is it?

00:19:50.752 --> 00:19:53.922
Complete silence again?
I'm bored of that already.

00:19:54.006 --> 00:19:57.050
Okay, so I'm not going to get
anything out of you, yeah?

00:19:57.134 --> 00:19:58.093
All right.

00:19:58.176 --> 00:19:59.886
-I'll just kill you, then--
-Wait!

00:20:01.930 --> 00:20:03.181
It's like you said.

00:20:03.724 --> 00:20:05.267
I'm an agent with the NCD.

00:20:05.976 --> 00:20:07.728
I went undercover to investigate.

00:20:07.811 --> 00:20:08.812
Got it.

00:20:08.895 --> 00:20:10.897
-Time to kill you!
-But why?

00:20:10.981 --> 00:20:13.817
If you kill an agent,
you'll get in deep shit.

00:20:13.900 --> 00:20:15.610
We already killed one.

00:20:15.694 --> 00:20:17.779
Killing one is one thing, but two?

00:20:17.863 --> 00:20:19.906
The NCD will never leave you alone.

00:20:19.990 --> 00:20:23.118
Is killing two really that different
from killing one?

00:20:23.201 --> 00:20:25.287
If I let you live,
they'll find out anyway.

00:20:25.370 --> 00:20:28.332
If you let me live,
I won't tell anyone what I saw here.

00:20:28.415 --> 00:20:30.876
-Such an obvious lie.
-It's not a damn lie!

00:20:30.959 --> 00:20:32.502
Watch your damn mouth!

00:20:32.586 --> 00:20:34.379
Sorry. It's not a lie.

00:20:34.463 --> 00:20:35.547
Too late. You're dead.

00:20:36.131 --> 00:20:37.257
In that case!

00:20:39.301 --> 00:20:40.886
How about we team up?

00:20:40.969 --> 00:20:41.928
What?

00:20:42.596 --> 00:20:45.140
Your group killed an agent, right?

00:20:45.223 --> 00:20:47.351
They'll find this place eventually.

00:20:48.268 --> 00:20:50.562
I'll just have some youngster
take the fall for it.

00:20:50.645 --> 00:20:52.481
It's the murder of an agent!

00:20:52.564 --> 00:20:53.982
It won't end with that.

00:20:54.524 --> 00:20:56.318
They'll do a thorough search.

00:20:57.402 --> 00:21:02.240
You'll have to halt business,
and worst case, you might get caught too.

00:21:03.742 --> 00:21:05.243
And what can you do about it?

00:21:05.327 --> 00:21:07.287
I can prevent that from happening.

00:21:07.371 --> 00:21:08.955
As if you could.

00:21:09.039 --> 00:21:10.165
I can!

00:21:11.249 --> 00:21:12.501
That's not all.

00:21:12.584 --> 00:21:16.296
From now on,
I'll leak the NCD's intel to you.

00:21:17.089 --> 00:21:20.634
Would you please let me be an S for you?

00:21:22.010 --> 00:21:22.844
What's an S?

00:21:23.762 --> 00:21:24.888
A spy.

00:21:25.555 --> 00:21:30.435
If we do that, you'll never get caught
and can make big money.

00:21:31.103 --> 00:21:33.647
How about it? I think it's a good deal.

00:21:34.940 --> 00:21:35.899
Got any proof?

00:21:36.650 --> 00:21:37.484
What?

00:21:37.567 --> 00:21:39.319
Proof that you're with the NCD.

00:21:40.445 --> 00:21:41.822
That's…

00:21:41.905 --> 00:21:44.199
Show me some ID
if you're really with them.

00:21:45.951 --> 00:21:46.952
I don't have it now.

00:21:47.035 --> 00:21:47.911
Why not?

00:21:48.662 --> 00:21:51.206
I can't carry it with me
while I'm undercover.

00:21:51.748 --> 00:21:52.791
All right.

00:21:53.291 --> 00:21:54.126
Your phone, then.

00:21:55.627 --> 00:21:57.421
If you're really with the NCD,

00:21:57.504 --> 00:22:00.340
you'll have mutual coworkers
with the other NCD guy.

00:22:01.091 --> 00:22:03.969
If their numbers
are in both of your phones,

00:22:04.052 --> 00:22:05.512
I'll trust you.

00:22:05.595 --> 00:22:09.057
However, if they aren't…

00:22:11.184 --> 00:22:12.436
it's over for you.

00:22:19.609 --> 00:22:22.904
If we fill the corpse with holes
and throw it in the sea,

00:22:23.447 --> 00:22:25.949
conger eels will swim inside it

00:22:26.741 --> 00:22:28.660
and swiftly turn it into bones.

00:22:29.870 --> 00:22:34.082
And then,
it will never rise to the surface again.

00:22:36.668 --> 00:22:38.378
It will be over with this.

00:22:41.173 --> 00:22:42.632
Right.

00:23:25.175 --> 00:23:26.384
He's dead.

00:23:26.468 --> 00:23:29.346
Being a dealer for him was part
of your undercover investigation?

00:23:29.429 --> 00:23:30.263
Yes.

00:23:30.347 --> 00:23:32.807
Please let me be your S!

00:23:32.891 --> 00:23:35.393
It's the police that protect
this country from threats.

00:23:35.477 --> 00:23:37.312
-Don't forget that.
-Yes, sir.

00:23:37.395 --> 00:23:39.689
This case belongs to the police.

00:23:39.773 --> 00:23:41.483
Fuck that!

00:23:42.192 --> 00:23:44.569
What do you take people's lives for?

00:23:45.237 --> 00:23:50.116
While you were trying to rack up points,
we were about to get killed!

00:23:50.909 --> 00:23:52.535
Results mean everything.

00:23:52.619 --> 00:23:55.121
I don't care about the life
of a punk like you.

00:23:55.205 --> 00:24:01.127
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS,
GROUPS, OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

00:24:01.211 --> 00:24:02.170
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan